LAB 11.5 — TEST SUITE SUMMARY

Student Name: Nguyễn Vy Anh
Student ID: HE194352
Project: Taskly App

1. Test Suite Overview

This test suite was created for the Taskly Flutter application. The purpose of the suite is to validate the application logic, user interface behavior, navigation behavior, and an end-to-end task editing flow.

2. Test Structure

The test folder is organized as follows:

test/
  unit/
    task_model_test.dart
    task_repository_test.dart

  widget/
    task_list_widget_test.dart
    task_navigation_test.dart
    task_integration_test.dart

  integration/
    task_integration_test.dart

3. Number of Tests

The test suite includes the following tests:

Unit Tests:
1. Task default completed value is false
2. Task toggle switches completed from false to true
3. Task toggle switches completed from true to false
4. TaskRepository addTask adds a task
5. TaskRepository deleteTask removes a task
6. TaskRepository updateTask updates an existing task

Widget Tests:
7. TaskListScreen shows empty state
8. TaskListScreen adds a task and updates UI
9. TaskListScreen adds multiple tasks and displays both

Navigation Test:
10. Tapping a task navigates to TaskDetailScreen

Integration Flow Test:
11. Add task, open detail screen, edit title, save, and verify updated title in list

4. Types of Tests

Unit Testing:
Used to test pure Dart logic in the Task model and TaskRepository.

Widget Testing:
Used to test UI rendering and user interaction in TaskListScreen.

Navigation Testing:
Used to test screen transition from TaskListScreen to TaskDetailScreen.

Integration-style Testing:
Used to simulate a complete user flow including adding, editing, saving, and verifying task updates.

5. Behaviors Validated

The test suite validates:
- Task completed value is false by default
- Task toggle works correctly
- TaskRepository can add tasks
- TaskRepository can delete tasks
- TaskRepository can update tasks
- Empty task list displays correct message
- User can add one task
- User can add multiple tasks
- User can open the detail screen
- Detail screen contains title “Task Detail”
- Detail screen contains TextField with key detailTitleField
- User can edit and save an updated task title

6. Known Limitations

The app currently stores data only in memory, so tasks are lost when the app is restarted. The integration test is implemented as a Flutter widget-based flow test instead of a full physical-device integration_test package. The app also does not include validation messages for empty task input.

7. Test Command

The full test suite can be executed using:

flutter test

8. Conclusion

The Taskly application has a complete test suite covering model logic, repository logic, UI behavior, navigation, and a full task editing flow. All required lab testing objectives were addressed.